    "condition": ["A","B","C","A","B","C","A","B","C"],
    "titer": [2.1, 2.4, 2.3, 2.0, 2.5, 2.6, 1.9, 2.2, 2.4]

display(df)

# ÌíÄÏù¥

```python
df_mean = df.groupby('condition')['titer'].mean().reset_index(name='mean_titer')

mean_A = df_mean[df_mean['condition']=='A']['mean_titer'].item()
df_mean['improvement_pct'] = (df_mean['mean_titer']-mean_A)/mean_A*100
best_condition, best_improvement = df_mean[['condition','improvement_pct']][df_mean['improvement_pct']==df_mean['improvement_pct'].max()].values[0]
display(df_mean, mean_A, best_condition, best_improvement)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,4))
color = np.where(df_mean['condition']=='A', 'gray', 'blue')
ax.bar(df_mean['condition'], df_mean['mean_titer'], color = color )
ax.set_title("Mean Titer by Condition")
ax.set_xlabel("Condition")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean_titer")
ax.grid(False)
ax.axhline(mean_A, linestyle='--', linewidth=2, color = 'gray')
```
